RETIRED Orlando Pirates goalkeeper Brilliant Khuzwayo visited Kaizer Chiefs chairman Kaizer Motaung at the Chiefs Village in Naturena on Thursday. Khuzwayo, took to Twitter to share his “priceless” moment with the Amakhosi chairman. WATCH: BUCS GOALIE'S CAREER OVER! “Today I shared a priceless moment with the Chairman of @KaizerChiefs. The wisdom and blessings came abundantly. The Village shall and always will be a home for me. One day I wish to own team also because he Dr Kaizer Motaung inspired me and he gave me the blessings today,” read Khuzwayo’s tweet. Khuzwayo joined Pirates from Chiefs in July last year, but never made a single appearance for Pirates before he was forced to retire due to a recurring ankle injury. 